race.comment: PLEASE ME DO (8) was comfortably accounted for when fifth last time out over 1450m at Kilmore, beaten 3 lengths. That followed a win at this track at the previous outing. Tackling a more suitable race so she is a major player. KING'S TAJ (2) finished out of the money when fresh from a spell two starts back then he was never in contention and was beaten 7 lengths when seventh in a 1300m contest at Ararat a week-and-a-half ago. Likely improver with strong prospects. KENTAHTEN (1) finished second last start over 1200m at Dunkeld, beaten a long neck. Suitably placed so anticipating a big run again. GOT OUT THE FENCE (7) has strung together some good runs this campaign, including a win two back and a narrow defeat in similar grade to this last start. Just needs luck from the shocking gate. HIGHLAND GEORGE (3) was out of the money when resuming from a spell last start over 1215m at Kyneton, beaten 6 lengths. Nicely placed to play a key role here.
